{"lemma":"غَيْرَة","slug":"غَيْرَة","root":"غ.#.ر","root_slug":"غ-_-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/غ-_-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n32615","n32722","n32721"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%BA%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of غَارَ (ḡāra, “to be jealous”) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"jealousy","examples":[{"text":"الْغَيْرَةُ غَالِبًا مَا تَنْبَعُ مِن مَشَاعِرِ الْنُّقْصِ أَوْ قِلَّةِ تَقْدِيرِ لِلْذَّاتِ، وَمُقَارَنَةُ الشَّخْصِ بِنَفْسِهِ بِاِسْتِمْرَارِ مَعَ الْآخَرِينَ وَالْشُّعُورِ بِأَنَّ لَدَيْهِمُ الْمَزِيدِ أَوْ أَفْضَلِ يُمْكِنُ أَنْ يُؤْدِيَ إِلَى مَشَاكِلِ إِضَافِيَّةٍ فِي مَجَالِ تَقْدِيرِ الذَّاتِ.","english":"Jealousy often stems from feelings of inadequacy or low self-esteem, and constantly comparing oneself to others and feeling that others have more or are better can lead to further self-esteem issues."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"zeal, fervor"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"solicitude: followed by عَلَى (ʕalā, “for”)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sense of honor, self-respect"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ɣaj.ra/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n32615","headword_ar":"غِيرَةٌ","root":"gwr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Abundance of the produce of the earth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miyrapN","text_ar":"مِيرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a provision of corn,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wheat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: belonging to this art. and to art."}